"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-team-gb-dressage-bronze-charlotte-dujardin-b1174596.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Carl Hester, Charlotte Fry and Becky Moody have won Olympic bronze forTeam GBin the dressage team Grand Prix Special.  Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  Winter escapes and activities to end the year in style  The British team qualified in third place behind Germany and Denmark, but took an early lead after Moody scored 76.489 per cent aboard Jagerbomb.  Hester was next up on Fame, slightly bettering Moody's mark with 76.520 per cent, with Charlotte Fry last to ride for Team GB with Glamourdale.  While she secured a score of 79.483 per cent, it was only good enough for third behind Germany and Denmark.  The bronze medal comes after a testing period for the British equestrian team, with three-time dressage gold-medal winnerCharlotte Dujardinhaving withdrawn from the Games just days before the opening ceremony, meaning reserve rider Moody stepped into the team.  Dujardin dropped out of Paris and was provisionally suspendedby equestrian's governing body, the International Federation for Equestrian Sports (FEI), pending an investigation into a video from four years ago which showed her repeatedly hitting a student's horse with a whip from the ground during a coaching session.  Hester, who enjoyed a long relationship with Dujardin as her mentor, said: \\\"It's been really difficult, very hard, and as I said before, we have had to put it out of our minds.  \\\"I have had to concentrate on the team and I am lucky in a way that I had Becky to deal with every day and help, which helps me focus on something else.  \\\"We have full-time jobs most of us, then you come here and you have one horse to ride and you are just going out of your mind with what not to think about all day and what to do all day.  \\\"It's been a long week but I feel fantastic now it's done.\\\"  While Hester was appearing at his seventhOlympics, Moody was enjoying a dream debut with her gelding Jagerbomb, who she bred herself.  She said: \\\"What an incredible stadium and the crowd were fantastic and my horse was a total legend.  \\\"I think because I bred him and we have done everything together, he's just a total dude - a lovely, lovely horse.  \\\"He's been quite spicy here this week and Carl has helped me out an awful lot to find that inner calm in both of us, but it has been fantastic and he's been amazing.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"